do while loop


Here’s a simple demonstration of while, do-while, and for loops in C — each shown separately 👇

⸻

a) While Loop

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int i = 1;

    printf("While loop:\n");
    while (i <= 5) {
        printf("%d\n", i);
        i++;
    }

    return 0;
}

Explanation:
	•	The loop checks the condition before executing.
	•	It prints numbers 1 to 5.

⸻

b) Do-While Loop

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int i = 1;

    printf("Do-While loop:\n");
    do {
        printf("%d\n", i);
        i++;
    } while (i <= 5);

    return 0;
}

Explanation:
	•	The loop executes at least once even if the condition is false.
	•	Prints numbers 1 to 5.

⸻

c) For Loop

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    printf("For loop:\n");
    for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
        printf("%d\n", i);
    }

    return 0;
}

Explanation:
	•	The for loop includes initialization, condition, and increment in one line.
	•	Prints numbers 1 to 5 in order.

